data.name: repeating_include
data.prompt: When updating a repeating event, this is a required field. Values are: "all" - updates all events in this series, "future" - updates this event and all that occur after, "none" - only updates a single event.

data.name: repeating_type_code
data.prompt: A code for the frequency of the repeated event, this is required with the "repeating_include" attribute when creating a repeating event. Valid values are: "1" - repeat an event daily, "2" - repeat an event weekly.

data.name: repeating_until
data.prompt: A date when the repeating event should end, this is inclusive so an event will be created on this day if it falls before the next event specified by "repeating_type_code". This attribute is required with "repeating_type_code" when creating a repeating event.

data.name: page_size
data.prompt: The number of items to return for each page. Sending this parameter with the query will enable paging for the returned collection.

data.name: page_number
data.prompt: The number of the page to be returned. This requires that paging be turned on by also providing the page_size parameter.

data.name: sort_start_date
data.prompt: Sort the returned dataset based on the start_date field, valid values are 'asc' or 'desc'.
